"{\"abstract\":\"Hair plays an important role in human appearance. However, hair segmentation is still a challenging problem partially due to the lack of an effective model to handle its arbitrary shape variations. In this paper, we present a part-based model robust to hair shape and environment variations. The key idea of our method is to identify local parts by promoting the effectiveness of the part-based model. To this end, we propose a measurable statistic, called Subspace Clustering Dependency (SC-Dependency), to estimate the co-occurrence probabilities between local shapes. SC-Dependency guarantees output reasonability and allows us to evaluate the effectiveness of part-wise constraints in an information-theoretic way. Then we formulate the part identification problem as an MRF that aims to optimize the effectiveness of the potential functions. Experiments are performed on a set of consumer images and show our algorithm's capability and robustness to handle hair shape variations and extreme environment conditions.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"144457723\",\"name\":\"Nan Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144457723\"},{\"authorId\":\"1679380\",\"name\":\"H. Ai\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1679380\"},{\"authorId\":\"145410701\",\"name\":\"F. Tang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145410701\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2770627\",\"name\":\"Ilkoo Ahn\"},{\"authorId\":\"145568138\",\"name\":\"Changick Kim\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/TMM.2016.2551698\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"7a09e8f65bd85d4c79f0ae90d4e2685869a9894f\",\"title\":\"Face and Hair Region Labeling Using Semi-Supervised Spectral Clustering-Based Multiple Segmentations\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/7a09e8f65bd85d4c79f0ae90d4e2685869a9894f\",\"venue\":\"IEEE Transactions on Multimedia\",\"year\":2016},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\